8.10	Yuktibhasa	Yuktibhāṣā	As per the old Indian tradition of starting off new chapters with elementary content, the first four chapters of the Yuktibhasa contain elementary mathematics, such as division, proof of Pythagorean theorem, square root determination, etc. The radical ideas are not discussed until the sixth chapter on circumference of a circle. Yuktibhasa contains the derivation and proof of the power series for inverse tangent, discovered by Madhava. In the text, Jyesthadeva describes Madhava's series in the following manner:	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d0/Yuktibhasa.gif
